<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
NOTE. The males described by Santschi (1921b) were captured in flight, not associated with workers or queens. Their identity as 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:138763" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Ponera abeillei André" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abeillei">abeillei</taxonomicName>
is therefore not assured, but is most probably correct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
